{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/pullrequests/35/comments/38049618.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/diff/ignitionrobotics/ign-common:7f52681e3f07..2a5a192f9e47?path=src%2FSystemPaths_TEST.cc"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/pull-requests/35/_/diff#comment-38049618"}}, "parent": {"id": 37948038, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/pullrequests/35/comments/37948038.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/pull-requests/35/_/diff#comment-37948038"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 35, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/pullrequests/35.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/pull-requests/35"}}, "title": "Added SystemPaths::FindFile overload that accepts a list of search paths"}, "content": {"raw": "I didn't use `std::tmpfile` because of [\"On some implementations (e.g. Linux), this function actually creates, opens, and immediately deletes the file from the file system\"](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/io/c/tmpfile). I didn't test this, but if the file is immediately deleted then I expect the open call on line 119 would fail.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I didn't use <code>std::tmpfile</code> because of <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/io/c/tmpfile\" rel=\"nofollow\">\"On some implementations (e.g. Linux), this function actually creates, opens, and immediately deletes the file from the file system\"</a>. I didn't test this, but if the file is immediately deleted then I expect the open call on line 119 would fail.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-06-01T20:54:19.636110+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Shane Loretz", "uuid": "{656e3311-aad9-45a1-aaf7-b0ee0e84b287}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B656e3311-aad9-